@node requirements "BMOD requirements"

BMOD requires following things:

	∑ @{" AHI audio system release v4. " link ahi}
	∑ AmigaOS release 2.
	∑ mc68020 recommended, but not required.
@endnode

@node features "BMOD features"

Major features found in BMOD:
	∑ AHI support (Aura, Delfina, DraCo, Prelude, Toccata, Wavetools)
	∑ low rastertime usage
	∑ small size
	∑ 255 samples
	∑ 131kB sample length
	∑ support for 256 effects (+ eXtended commands)
	∑ support for 256 effect values
	∑ support for 65535 positions, currently at 256
	∑ support for 65535 patterns, currently at 256
	∑ eXtended command column
	∑ very system friendly
	∑ can use fastmem
	∑ deltaed samples
	∑ internal realtime pattern unpacking

Minor features:
	∑ mc68030-optimizations
	∑ songname-length 32 chars
	∑ samplename-length 32 chars
	∑ works with serial transfers
	∑ very versile and expandable
	∑ asm-source included and it's very easy to understand
	  (comments included =)
	∑ future support

Tested with:
	∑ a1200/030/50Mhz CPU/8MB Fast/200MB HD (my machine)
		- Old Commodore model
		- Blizzard 1230IV
	∑ a1200/030/882/50Mhz CPU&FPU/16MB Fast/1GB HD/CDROM
		- Old Commodore model
		- Blizzard 1230III
@endnode

